deck: Director Radcliffe was Cecil Stedman's boss before Cecil took over as director
description:
Character

Director Radcliffe first appears in Invincible #50 in a special origin story explaining how Cecil went from agent to director. The Director shows Cecil that protecting the world is not so black and white when Cecil is saved by the very same people who caused him to get his facial scar (Order of the Freeing Fist), Cecil kills them but afterwards is jailed and then given the director job after Radcliffe because Radcliffe believes he will make the best replacement.

Powers & Abilities

Director Radcliffe shows no super powers but possesses great leadership and showed competency with firearms when fighting Lizard League.
name: Director Radcliffe

deck: A bar-maid and dear friend to Bodie Troll
description:
Character

Cholly first appears in Bodie Troll #1 - Bodie's Bargain and is best friends with the little troll and works for Miz Bijou. Cholly is sweet, kind and patient with nearly everyone, especially Bodie who often acts out and causes some trouble for numerous people, Miz Bijou included.

Cholly works as a bar-mad for Miz Bijou but also has done work as an actress with Bodie assisting her, it is in that same story arc where we learn that Cholly seems immune to magic as she uses magic lip stick given to her by Miz Bijou to transform Bodie; he changes to bubbles, a root, a couch, manure, a human girl and a human guy, however, when Bodie attempted to retaliate and show Cholly what it was like, the lip stick had no effect.

Powers & Abilities

Cholly is quick witted and kind, she is liked by just about everyone in Hagadorn. She also seems to be immune to magic.
name: Cholly

deck: A fairy godmother turned restaurant owner
description:
Character

Miz Bijou runs a tavern with the help of Cholly and she once worked as a fairy godmother but also retains much of her magical power which she transmits through a spatula.

Powers & Abilities

Bijou possess magical knowledge, power items (including the magic lipstick Cholly used to transform Bodie Troll), and the ability to control magic.
name: Miz Bijou

deck: The former ruler of the planet Viltrum,who, according to Thragg, was killed by Thaedus.
description:
Character History

Argall was the ruler of the Viltrumite Empire before Grand Regent Thragg and it was later determined his bloodline connected directly to that of Nolan & Mark Grayson. According to Thragg, Thaedus who was the former leader of the Coalition of Planets was the one who killed Lord Argall.

Powers & Abilities

Lord Argall is a Viltrumite so he would have all the same powers as them; Super Strength, Super Speed, Flight, Healing, Invulnerability as well as being a well trained combatant.

Lord Argall and his bloodline are also supposed to be highly resistant to the deadly Scourge Virus which killed nearly all of the Viltrumite people.
name: Lord Argall

deck: Madame Apsara is the manager of a resort spa by day. By night, she sheds her body and becomes a Krasue.
description:
Origin

Madame Apsara is a member of the Krasue, a race of vampires who appear as a human woman by day. At night they undergo the transformation to a Krasue. Madame Apsara ran the Jai Dam Resort & Spa in Thailand, which serviced many foreign businessmen. Vampirella met Madame Apsara while on the hunt for a Krasue and decided to stay at the spa for relaxation. At night, Vampirella was attacked by the Krasue and rescued from it by Lord Drago, her companion at that time. Together, they found the body of Madame Apsara, to which the Krasue had to return by daylight, or it would be destroyed. With the body, they lured the Krasue and trapped it. Vampirella killed Madame Apsara by removing her heart and drinking the blood of the Krasue.
name: Madame Apsara

deck: Ragdoll is a creature put together from parts of abused women. These parts scream for vengeance, which Ragdoll gladly carries out.
description:
Origin

Ragdoll is a creature put together from parts of abused women. These parts scream for vengeance, which Ragdoll gladly carries out.

One such woman is Gina, the servant of Ludwig Hertz. Carrying his child, he killed her, sliced her into pieces and sold her body parts to two men of questionable reputation. Her belly, with the heart-shaped birth mark, ended up part of Ragdoll.
